  "texts": [
    "In the first regime, for t < t ðnÞ min, the slope of the voltage trajectory starts with a value A ðnÞ i and increases or decreases after each spike arrival, depending on the sign of W ðnÞ ij, whereas at the time t = t ðnÞ min the potential enters the second regime, switching the slope to a fixed positive value B ðnÞ i.",
    "When the potential V ðnÞ i reaches the threshold ϑ ðnÞ i, neuron i generates a spike at time t ðnÞ and sends it to the next layer.",
    "The threshold ϑ ðnÞ i is defined as",
    "i À D ðnÞ i where D ðnÞ i is a trainable parameter initialized at 0 and e ϑ ðnÞ i is a fixed base threshold, defined to be large enough to prevent firing before t ðnÞ min, see Supplementary Note 2.",
    "Importantly, we also define t ðnÞ max, such that for t ≥ t ðnÞ max emission of a spike is impossible, e.g., implemented by a de-charging current for t ≥ t ðnÞ max which resets the membrane potential to zero (Fig. 1c)."
